01/05/2009
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The leadership of the Democratic Party of Socialists (DPS) decided late on Thursday (April 30th) to nominate the party's president, Milo Djukanovic, as the country's next prime minister. 
It will be Djukanovic's sixth term. 
The DPS also backed Socialist Democratic Party head Ranko Krivokapic as parliamentary speaker. 
President Filip Vujanovic is scheduled meet on Friday with opposition parties and hear their views regarding the nominations. 
(MIA, RTCG - 30/04/09)
